parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become stuck in gear, leading to accidents, injuries, or strandings.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
stalls
or becomes stuck in gear
the transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear
the vehicle rolls backward or forward unexpectedly
the transmission warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the shifter cable bushing can cause the vehicle to become stuck in gear, roll backward or forward unexpectedly, or prevent the vehicle from shifting into gear, leading to accidents, injuries, or strandings.
symptoms: The vehicle becomes stuck in gear
the vehicle rolls backward or forward unexpectedly
the shift lever becomes disconnected
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear
the shifter cable bushing breaks or fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of clutch and transmission components can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become stuck in gear, leading to accidents, injuries, or strandings.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
stalls
or becomes stuck in gear
the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure and detachment of the windshield can cause water leaks, reduced visibility, and increased risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Water leaking into the vehicle
windshield damage
windshield cracking
windshield detaching from the vehicle
excessive condensation build-up around the windshield area.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Panoramic Roof Panel Failure and Detachment
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure and detachment of the panoramic roof panel can cause wind noise, water leaks, and increased risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Air rushing into the cabin via the glass roof
the front edge of the glass roof panel is loose
the glass panel comes up at least a half inch when pushed.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Recall Repair Issues and Parts Distribution Disconnect
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay or inability to complete recall repairs can cause extended downtime, inconvenience, and potential safety risks.
symptoms: Parts not available
recall repairs not completed
extended wait times for repairs
vehicles left at dealerships for extended periods.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The glare on the windshield can cause reduced visibility, eye strain, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Glare on the windshield
difficulty seeing while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door latch can cause the door to open while the vehicle is in motion, which can lead to accidents or injuries to passengers or other road users.
symptoms: The door does not latch correctly
the door opens while the vehicle is in motion
the door falls off when opened or closed
the rail is bent due to repeated pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the panoramic roof glass panel can cause the glass to dislodge and fall off while driving, which can lead to accidents or injuries to passengers or other road users.
symptoms: The glass panel dislodges and falls off while driving
the glass panel is improperly bonded
water leaks into the vehicle through the roof.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The visibility issues can cause accidents or near-misses due to obstructed views or glare.
symptoms: The shift indicator or turn signal indicators are obscured
the brushed aluminum on the steering wheel and plastic around the radio and vents reflect sunlight
creating a glare.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delays in recall repairs can cause safety risks to continue, leading to potential accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle is left at the dealership for an extended period
the dealership is unable to secure the necessary parts
the manufacturer declines authorization to repair at the time.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the panoramic roof window can cause the glass panel to lift out of the recessed window frame, potentially leading to accidents or damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: The panoramic roof window starts lifting up along the leading edge of the glass panel
the panel comes completely out of the recessed window frame.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Ineffective Recall Repair for Active Windshield
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The ineffective repair of the active windshield can lead to compromised windshield integrity, potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The recall repair for the active windshield does not effectively solve the documented recall problem
the windshield may crack or shatter.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The swollen lug nuts can make it difficult or impossible to change a flat tire, potentially leading to accidents or strandings.
symptoms: The lug nuts are too big to fit with a wrench
moisture gets into the 2-part lug nuts
causing them to swell.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear hatch latch can cause the hatch to not close properly, potentially leading to accidents or damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: The rear hatch does not latch when closed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front brakes can cause the brakes to lock up, potentially leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The front brakes lock up
a burning smell comes from the front passenger wheel
the brakes may need to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The shattering of the sunroof can cause damage to the vehicle and potentially lead to injuries.
symptoms: The sunroof shatters.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to shift into park unexpectedly, potentially leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The shift light blinks on and off
the vehicle shifts into park while in motion
the vehicle will not shift out of park.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The windshield leak can cause water to pour into the vehicle, potentially leading to accidents or damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: Water leaks into the vehicle through the windshield
the leak is extreme and cannot be driven on a rainy day.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The carbon monoxide poisoning can cause the driver to lose consciousness, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The driver experiences a smell of exhaust fumes
the driver may black out or lose consciousness.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Hydraulic Control Unit (HCU) Pump Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Brake Hydraulic Control Unit (HCU) pump can cause the vehicle to abruptly stop, lose motive power, or have unintended deceleration, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle decelerates unintendedly
the brakes lock up
the brakes seize
the vehicle vibrates
the rotors overheat
the ABS
stability control
and traction control warning lights illuminate
and the brakes do not release pressure upon depressing the brake pedal.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to unintended deceleration, loss of motive power, or accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brakes lock up
the brakes seize
the vehicle vibrates
and debris is found in the brake lines.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Electronic Stability Control (ESC) system can cause the vehicle to lose traction, stability, or control, leading to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The ABS
stability control
and traction control warning lights illuminate
and the vehicle experiences unintended deceleration or loss of motive power.
